content: Hi all, my name is Tish Shute (Leichliter). I began in spatial computing very early in my career with robotics, using the programming language Forth - an interesting language that speaks machine and human efficiently. Currently, I work at Futurewei Technologies and I'm focused on the open web for spatial computing with Rust/Web Assembly as the foundation. I'm so excited that Rust/Wasm can enable an open approach to the spatial web at a time when reality is increasingly becoming the platform for computing.
